// Tutorial 10 — Flags and guards
//
// Flags are variables that control which rules fire.
//   [count=4]     → set flag "count" to 4
//   when count-1  → decrement count, fire only if count > 0
//
// This creates controlled repetition:
// the rule fires 4 times, then falls through to the default.

@core
@controls
@alphabet.western:browser

S -> Loop [count=4]

-----

when count-1 Loop -> C4 D4 E4 F4 Loop [mode:random]
when count-1 Loop -> E4 F4 G4 A4 Loop
Loop -> C5 _ _ _
